(4, 99, '7 Ivanti best practices for Hardware Asset Management', '7-ivanti-best-practices-for-hardware-asset-management', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In accordance with the technological advancement in this era, almost all companies utilize hardware to aid the company’s business process. Therefore, to manage it properly...</span></p>', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">In accordance with the technological advancement in this era, almost all companies utilize hardware to aid the company’s business process. Therefore, to manage it properly</span> there are a few best practices that businesses can use to manage the company’s hardware assets better. Hardware management is crucial to keep the hardware functioning properly. Ivanti has 7 best practices for Hardware Asset Management.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Despite having enough resources, 50% of organizations utilize 12 or more discovery tools to aid their business process. This means that what the companies are doing is inefficient as the staffs have to keep an eye on all of the discovery tools to summarize the report. The best practice to reach hardware asset management breadth is to get to a single point of truth by comparing data sets, normalizing, and reconciling by an automated process to drive accuracy. Regarding depth, 66% of IT managers do not have an accurate record of their IT assets. Not having accurate data of the IT assets may lead to not optimizing them properly, and therefore may result in loss of profit for the company. The best practice to achieve better depth is to reduce the complexity, define what is useful to track. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Companies not utilizing the full potential of their assets is also due to 30% of the assets are considered as “ghost” assets, meaning that the assets are missing or could not be found. It is best if the company knows who the asset is assigned to, drive accountability and compliance. In regards to naming convention, companies typically spend 10 or more hours each week to resolve data accuracy issues which are not efficient. To improve efficiency, hardware should be made identifiable using consistent naming conventions and implement normalization processes. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">For performance metrics, only a quarter of enterprises will be satisfied with the value that their ITAM provides. The lack of satisfaction could be alleviated by defining the business case to clearly articulate the value of ITAM investments that will contribute to the company’s specific business objectives. In regards to the company’s major process areas, 53% of all data lost and systems downtime is caused by hardware failure. Thus to achieve the best practice, the company should manage the hardware with process and policy throughout its lifecycle. Companies also often have multiple owners that are responsible for hardware assets, including IT, finance, line-of-business, or facilities management. This may lead to increased risks as each division is working separately on hardware management. In order to alleviate risks from working with multiple stakeholders, it is best if the company collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify risks, costs, and value.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In conclusion, most companies in this era utilize hardware assets to help their business process. Therefore, to optimize and care for hardware assets properly, Ivanti has 7 best practices for hardware asset management. The 7 best practices are: reach hardware asset management breadth is to get to a single point of truth by comparing data sets, normalizing, and reconciling by an automated process to drive accuracy, reduce the complexity and define what is useful to track, know who the asset is assigned to in order to drive accountability and compliance, hardware should be made identifiable using consistent naming conventions and implement normalization processes, define the business case to clearly articulate the value of ITAM investments that will contribute to the company’s specific business objectives, manage the hardware with process and policy throughout its lifecycle, collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify risks, costs and value. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">For more information about Ivanti solution, </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">contact us by phone at +62 21 3861 772, by</span><a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=628111221789&amp;text=Hallo%20PT%20Realta...\"> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Official Whatsapp</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> at +62 811 1221 789 (</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">chat only</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-w