(9, 97, 'Ivanti Asset Manager: Managing Company’s IT Assets from Purchase to Disposal for Complete Asset Optimization', 'ivanti-asset-manager-managing-company-s-it-assets-from-purchase-to-disposal-for-complete-asset-optimization', '<p class=\"intro-readmore\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Arial; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In this technological era, keeping track of IT assets is challenging for IT teams as hardware and software are assigned, reassigned, and moved from one location to another depending on business dynamics...</span></p>', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In this technological era, keeping track of IT assets is challenging for IT teams as hardware and software are assigned, reassigned, and moved from one location to another depending on business dynamics. Knowing what assets the company has and where they reside, tracking contracts and regulatory compliance, and gaining visibility into the cost of ownership are just the tip of the management iceberg to fully utilize the IT assets owned. Therefore it is necessary to deploy software that could help the company manage IT assets owned by the company. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-4d02e804-7fff-84f3-90fa-7a486ff29180\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </b></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Due to the complexity of discovering, tracking, and managing hardware, many organizations today still are not tracking their IT assets effectively. Therefore some of them are still using spreadsheets to keep track of their assets and only verifying the location of their fixed assets occasionally. It is imperative to monitor assets from procurement to disposal to know where they are and how they perform so it is possible to make the most out of the IT investment. The availability of software for IT asset management will remove the complexities of the IT asset management process and own complete asset management. Asset Manager is capable of simplifying the process of producing a single report, searching, and tracking assets with an Asset Repository. Through Asset Manager, it is possible to achieve consistent management from request to purchase order, receipt, deployment, and finally disposal. This makes it easy to allow the assignment of asset information, including identifying data, lifecycle status, stock, location, and warranty information. Thus, tracking asset availability, and performance. As the organization grows, evolves, or users change roles the task of tracking assets and their performance becomes increasingly difficult. To maintain repository accuracy, Asset Manager includes powerful data-importing capabilities that allow imported data from several discovery sources, including Ivanti Neurons, Ivanti Endpoint Manager, Ivanti Data Center Discovery, and many more. Through the Asset Manager mobile app, IT assets are manageable at any time from anywhere. Search for assets by serial number, tag, device name, user, or location and update fields as necessary. Viewing user’s profile, check for incidents on the devices, and apply automated quick actions is possible to be done while working remotely or on the move. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </b></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Achieve faster updating and quick data retrieval with Ivanti’s barcode scanning capability. Scan assets to look up or modify the information or scan multiple assets to update information in Asset Manager as part of your asset-tracking discipline. With Ivanti, it’s simple to store and view procurement data. Owning accurate, timely financial, and contractual information helps the company to optimize asset purchases in the way the business needs. Take the guesswork out of asset refresh requirements by calculating and tracking asset age and value and gain cost and contract visibility. View and manage the complete list of contracts in the company’s environment tied to individual assets. Utilizing Ivanti’s Asset Manager, the catalog of maintained authorized items could be used to increase speed to provision while reducing service desk calls, therefore enhancing the user experience through a product catalog. Using the catalog, the increase of speed to provision while reducing service desk calls is possible. Eliminate frustrations that lead to shadow IT and subsequent asset management complexity. Ivanti Asset Manager ensures that the company can organize asset availability proactively to meet business and user requests. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </b></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ivanti Asset Manager is capable of storing vendor information to ensure the company is managing strategic vendors effectively and drive vendor management. The company is able to keep track of vendor interactions by logging comments about their service and the assets they provide. Through this, the company then will be able to determine whether the company is getting the most out of your investments or if it’s time to terminate relationships. Ivanti Asset Manager is also highly configurable to suit your needs. This solution is available on both on-premise and cloud. Rest assured that many years of Ivanti asset management experience and the best practices of industry organizations such as IAITAM are at the heart of the Asset Manager solution. Ivanti Asset Manager is built on the proven Ivanti Service Manager platform, leveraging a mature user interface and offering a strong foundation for growth. Asset Manager enhances change management processes and policies by providing status updates to IT assets in context to help maximize productivity. After implementation, users will benefit from a rich self-service experience as they navigate easily through an approved service catalog, alleviating pressure on IT staff.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </b></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In conclusion, the management of IT assets is challenging in this technological era due to the high rate of turnovers of hardware and software assigned. Thus the company will benefit tremendously from the deployment of IT Asset Management software. This is because Ivanti Asset Manager is capable of managing the company’s IT assets from purchase to disposal for complete asset optimization, tracking asset availability and performance, managing assets while on the move, achieving faster updates with barcode scanning, gaining cost and contract visibility, delivering enhanced user experiences with a product catalog, driving vendor management, being highly configurable to suit the company’s needs, and integrate with Service Manager for improved service delivery. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; tex